        "description": {
            "value": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; width: 655.175px; padding: 0px; color: #1c1c1c; font-family: Vollkorn, Eczar, Georgia, serif; font-size: 15.6px; margin: var(--p-space, 1em) auto 0px auto;\">The philosophy of Sangpotshi, also known as the River of Life, centers around concepts of fate, karma, and cyclic reincarnation. Adherents believe each soul is judged upon its actions in life, and these actions determine its station when it returns to the living world. This cycle repeats until the soul reaches its perfected form through the accrual of experience and wisdom, whereupon it passes on to Pharasma's court and the afterlife to come.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; width: 655.175px; padding: 0px; color: #1c1c1c; font-family: Vollkorn, Eczar, Georgia, serif; font-size: 15.6px; margin: var(--p-space, 1em) auto 0px auto;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Edicts</strong> live selflessly; heed the wisdom of the learned, the wise, and those in stations of authority</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; width: 655.175px; padding: 0px; color: #1c1c1c; font-family: Vollkorn, Eczar, Georgia, serif; font-size: 15.6px; margin: var(--p-space, 1em) auto 0px auto;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Anathema</strong> needlessly break significant traditions, actively interfere with the perfection efforts of another soul or allow others to do so</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; width: 655.175px; padding: 0px; color: #1c1c1c; font-family: Vollkorn, Eczar, Georgia, serif; font-size: 15.6px; margin: var(--p-space, 1em) auto 0px auto;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Areas of Concern</strong> fate, karma, and reincarnation</p>"
